Frequently Asked Questions for Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. (NYSE:AVAL)
What is Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A.'s stock symbol?

Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "AVAL."



How often does Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A.?

Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. announced a monthly dividend on Monday, April 3rd. Stockholders of record on Monday, May 1st will be paid a dividend of $0.0339 per share on Wednesday, May 10th. This represents a $0.41 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 4.65%. The ex-dividend date is Thursday, April 27th.  View Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A.'s Dividend History.



How were Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A.'s earnings last quarter?

Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. (NYSE:AVAL) posted its earnings results on Tuesday, November, 29th. The company reported $0.19 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of $0.15 by $0.04. The business had revenue of $1.41 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.36 billion. Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. had a net margin of 8.82% and a return on equity of 10.18%.  View Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A.'s Earnings History.



Who are some of Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A.'s key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. include Regions Financial Corporation (RF), Credicorp (BAP), Huntington Bancshares Incorporated (HBAN), Banco De Chile (BCH), Banco Santander-Chile (BSAC), Comerica Incorporated (CMA), BanColombia S.A. (CIB), CIT Group Inc (DEL) (CIT), SVB Financial Group (SIVB), East West Bancorp (EWBC), Signature Bank (SBNY), Grupo Supervielle SA -ADR (SUPV), New York Community Bancorp (NYCB), Cullen/Frost Bankers (CFR), Commerce Bancshares (CBSH), PacWest Bancorp (PACW), Bank of the Ozarks (OZRK) and Synovus Financial Corp. (SNV).



