Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. (AVAL) Ex-Dividend Date Scheduled for July 27, 2017


July 26, 2017, 09:00:03 AM EDT
By NASDAQ.com News









































Shutterstock photo


Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. ( AVAL  ) will begin trading ex-dividend on July 27, 2017. A cash dividend payment of $0.034 per share is scheduled to be paid on August 09, 2017. Shareholders who purchased AVAL prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment. This marks the 5th quarter that AVAL has paid the same dividend. At the current stock price of $8.68, the dividend yield is 4.7%. The previous trading day's last sale of AVAL was $8.68, representing a -3.98% decrease from the 52 week high of $9.04 and a 20.89% increase over the 52 week low of $7.18. AVAL is a part of the Finance sector, which includes companies such as Royal Bank Of Canada ( RY  ) and Banco Santander, S.A. ( SAN  ). AVAL's current earnings per share, an indicator of a company's profitability, is $.69. Zacks Investment Research reports AVAL's forecasted earnings growth in 2017 as 3.62%, compared to an industry average of 6.8%. For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the AVAL Dividend History  page. Our  Dividend Calendar  has the full list of stocks that have an ex-dividend today.  Interested in gaining exposure to AVAL through an Exchange Traded Fund [ETF]?   The following ETF(s) have AVAL as a top-10 holding:  First Trust International IPO ETF (   FPXI    ).  The top-performing ETF of this group is FPXI with an increase of 21.83% over the last 100 days. It also has the highest percent weighting of AVAL at 1.29%.



