Grupo Aval Acciones Y Valores S.A. Key Developments

Grupo Aval Acciones Y Valores S.A. Reports Earnings Results for the First Quarter of 2017; Provides Financial Guidance for the Year 2017
May 31 17
Grupo Aval Acciones Y Valores S.A. reported earnings results for the first quarter of 2017. Attributable net income for the quarter was COP 587 billion or COP 26 per share, a 25.8% higher than the first quarter 2016 result. Excluding the onetime attributable wealth tax payment, attributable net income for the quarter was COP 661 billion or COP 29 per share. The company's ROAE and ROAA for the quarter were 15.4% and 1.6%, respectively. On quarterly basis, net interest income grew 9.6% from COP 2.4 trillion in the first quarter of 2016 to COP 2.6 trillion during the first quarter of 2017. It increased by 9.4% versus the last quarter of 2016. Gross fee income grew by 7.2% compared to the same period a year earlier and decreased by 0.2% compared to the previous quarter. 


For the year 2017, the company expects return on average equity to be approximate 14% to 14.5%, primarily due to additional provisions in reference to Electricaribe. The company expects full year net interest margin to be in the 5.7 area and NIM on loans to be in the 6.6% to 6.7% range.


Grupo Aval Acciones Y Valores S.A., Q1 2017 Earnings Call, May 31, 2017
May 22 17
Grupo Aval Acciones Y Valores S.A., Q1 2017 Earnings Call, May 31, 2017


Grupo Aval Acciones Y Valores S.A. to Report Q1, 2017 Results on May 30, 2017
Apr 28 17
Grupo Aval Acciones Y Valores S.A. announced that they will report Q1, 2017 results After-Market on May 30, 2017


