Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S (NYSE:AVAL) Sees Unusual Trading Volume in Its Shares - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S (NYSE:AVAL) Sees Unusual Trading Volume in Its Shares
July 24, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





(NYSE:AVAL) shares saw light trading volume with 3,006 shares changing hands by the end of trading on Tuesday.  Shares saw a steep decrease in trading volume of 98.11% under the normal average daily volume. 
 Here are a few additional firms who have increased or decreased their stake in (AVAL).   Aperio Group, LLC grew its ownership by buying 56,441 shares an increase of 35.7% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Aperio Group, LLC now holds 214,471 shares worth $1,776,000. The total value of its holdings increased 37.6%. As of the end of the quarter Bank Of Montreal /can/ had bought 35,900 shares growing its holdings by 485.1%. The value of the investment in (AVAL) increased from $60,000 to $359,000 a change of $299,000 quarter over quarter.
 As of quarter end Morgan Stanley had acquired  a total of 3,593 shares growing its stake by 24.6%. The value of the investment in AVAL went from $116,000 to $149,000 increasing 28.4% since the last quarter. As of quarter end Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) had disposed of 1,753 shares trimming its position 100.0%. The value of the investment in Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S decreased from $14,000 to $0 a change of 100.0% quarter to quarter.
  On March 29 the company was changed to a “Neutral” according to a Goldman Sachs report which was a cut from the previous “Buy” rating. On January 6, 2016 the stock rating was rated “Underweight” by JP Morgan a cut from the previous “Neutral” rating.
 On June 10 Morgan Stanley made no change to the stock rating of “Overweight” and lowered the price expectation from $12.50 to $11.50.
 In the market the company is trading down by -0.58% since yesterday’s close of $8.64.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S declared a dividend payable on Wednesday August 9th, 2017.  The dividend will be $0.103 per share for the quarter which comes to $0.41 on an annualized basis.  This dividend represents a yeild of $4.71 which is the dividend as a percentage of the current share price.  The ex-dividend date will be Thursday June 29th, 2017. 





 It is trading at $8.59 marginally over the 50 day moving average of $8.35 and a tad above the 200 day moving average of $8.18.  The 50 day moving average moved up $0.24 and the 200 day average moved up $0.41. 
 The P/E ratio is 13.42 and the market value is 9.57B.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $0.64 and is projected to be $0.72 for the current year with 1,114,050,000 shares now outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted at $0.18 with next year’s EPS projected to be $0.78. 
 Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. provides a range of financial services and products to public and private sector customers in Colombia and Central America. It operates in four segments: Banco De BogotÃ¡, Banco De Occidente, Banco AV Villas, and Banco Popular. The company offers various deposit products and services, including checking accounts, savings accounts, and time deposits, as well as other deposits consisting primarily of transactional accounts, cashier checks, and collection services. It also provides loan products, such as commercial loans that comprise general purpose loans, working capital loans, loans funded by development banks, corporate credit cards, and overdraft loans; consumer loans comprising personal loans, automobile and other vehicle loans, credit cards, overdrafts, loans funded by development banks, and general purpose loans; microcredit loans; and mortgage loans. In addition, the company offers pension and severance fund management services; and fiduciary, bonded warehousing and brokerage transactions, real estate escrow services, merchandise and document storage and deposit, customs agency, cargo management, surety bond and merchandise distribution services, bancassurance, and payment and collection services, as well as engages in deposit and lending operations in foreign currencies. Further, it is involved in merchant and investment banking activities; trading activities that include fixed income trading, derivatives, and foreign exchange operations, as well as the provision of treasury services, pension plan administration, investment fund advice, financial advisory, leasing, private banking, and insurance services. As of December 31, 2015, the company operated a network of 1,433 branches and 3,808 ATMs in Colombia; and 352 branches and 1,815 ATMs in Central America. Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. was founded in 1870 and is based in BogotÃ¡, Colombia..






